This paper deals with improving the performance of neural machine translation (NMT) by incorporating pre-specified bilingual pairs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also proposes methods to modify the training data and embeddings, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper experiments with improving the attention mechanism, which is a common technique used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with language translation, which is a common application of computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
